My favorite place to visit when I'm in Wisconsin. Their tastings are cheap! Only $10 for 5 tastings or there is another option just if you wanted two beers. They expanded the lodge and bar. There is also bar service outside that serves the patio. I love coming here to stock up on all of the cool lienenkugel gear. There are so many cool things in the gift shop, more than any other place and there is definitely something for EVERYONE in the gift shop. One of the really cool things about the lodge is that they have different mixed beer creations.My favorite taster is the pink lemonade (50% berry and 50% summer shandy). It's a really nice place to visit on a cool day. Their pretzels are also DELICIOUS the mustard that they provide you is FANTASTIC! It is a MUST when in Wisconsin.

I might be willing to attend a tour again on a day the place is running. Plus, more beer!

We have lived in Chetek for 20 years.  Occasionly, over that time we have brought our family and friends to Leines for a visit.  Apparenty, Leinies is going broke from slow beer sales that they now need to charge $12 per for a tour and a couple of small samples.   This was free for many years.  All the items in the gift shop are exorbitant.  It's all about the cash....Sad. I was very disappointed.  This was a great outting at one time.  At least Irvine Park is still a hit with the grandkids.

I finally got to go inside, I had never made it here before while it was open. I was a little surprised by it. I thought this was a restaurant and bar, but it is a gift ship and sampling area. After hiking in the area, we stopped in to get one drink each, but apparently you can't do that here, you have to get at least two each, or five samples. Now I know for next time. It's a beautiful area, and a nice place to visit. It would be nice if they let you get just one drink though, instead of having to buy multiple drinks.

I visited the Leine Lodge in October with my family, including kids, and very much enjoyed the tour. The tour was one of the more thorough and informative brewery tours I've been on. Plus, you get 2 pints or 5 5-oz samples at the end. The kids even had a good time learning about the various steps in the process. The tour takes between 45 minutes and an hour, depending upon how many questions are asked.  I recommend a tour of the Leine's to anyone interested in beer, or local culture.

While MillerCoors does own Leinenkugel's, you won't see any evidence of that at the Leinie Lodge. The Lodge still feels very small-town and friendly with lots of merchandise for sale and small museum-like cases scattered amongst the building.  Just inside the front doors, you are greeted with the option of a $5 tour of the brewery grounds (that lasts about 45 minutes) and a bracelet that allows for five beer tastings (the $5 includes a free "Official Taste Tester" glass). I have never been on this particular brewery tour, but have done the tastings several times. The bracelet lets you choose from four of their many beers on tap (including a menu they have in which they mix different beers). The "Pink Lemonade" beer mix is sweet, but a crowd favorite. The fifth and final tasting is their Big Eddy special brew, which is always changing. I have had the Royal Nektar and Russian Imperial Stout, both have been amazing.  Carrie, our bartender from our most recent visit, was the nicest bartender I have met. She was very knowledgeable, let me try a couple samples of new brews, and even set my daughter up with her own taster of lemonade. It was her great service that compelled to write this review.  My wife and I have decided to make the Leinie Lodge a traditional stop when passing the Eau Claire / Chippewa Falls area on our way home to the cities. If you are driving that area of I-94, I would recommend a visit. It’s well worth the 7 mile detour.

So here are some facts - Jake Leinenkugel is no longer in charge. Leinenkugel's not your independent Northwoods brewery - its a wholly owned subsidiary of Miller Coors. While New Glarus remains independent the Leinenkugels have cashed out. The beer is good but the tours are weak. Stick to the $5 tasting and the store
